---
source: crates/carta/tests/golden_e2e.rs
expression: output
---
<p>Emphasis stays literal in "*quoted emphasis*" and strong in "**quoted
strong**".</p>
<p>Angle brackets also suppress markup as in &lt;*not emphasis*&gt;.</p>
<p>Interpreted text in "`quoted interpreted text`" stays literal.</p>
<p>A phrase reference in "`quoted phrase`_" and a simple reference in
"link_" stay literal.</p>
<p>An inline literal "<code>stays code</code>" because literals are
never suppressed.</p>
